VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'at time. Well, it\'s back as kind of the Photoshop of video. Uh, yeah, a really promising video editor you got to check out and it\'s free. Good stuff here. Plus, a preview of 3D conditioned AI video. Uh yeah, this one is really'

[00:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'exciting. All right, let\'s hop in. Kicking off, we have a super fast video model that just dropped. Uh this one is called Lucy 14B and comes to us from Deart, who you might remember as the'

[00:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'folks that brought us Oasis. Uh it was kind of one of the first uh real-time generative openw world models. This one was the like the Minecraft one very early in. Well, today they\'ve released Lucy 14b, a hyper optimized video model.'

[00:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Uh this one is image to video uh generating at unprecedented speeds. Yeah, they\'re claiming generations at uh 6.26 seconds uh compared to like VO3'

[01:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'fast uh at 54 seconds, which actually seemed high to me. So I just ran a test uh running on a VO generation and yeah, uh 1 minute 5 seconds. So slower than I actually thought it was. But does fast'

[01:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'matter if it\'s not good or cheap? Like the old saying goes, fast, cheap, good? can only pick two. Thus far, the only place that I\'ve actually seen the model at work is over on fall. I\'m sure that it will roll out as time goes on. Lucy'

[01:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'is running at a cost of 8 cents per second, so you know, actually fairly reasonable. Um, so loading in our image of our uh couple in love who have just discovered that they live in a'

[01:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'simulation. Um, and then yeah, giving that a run. Uh, prompt here is just man and woman talking in love. Joyful. Yeah, the generation does come in pretty quickly. Uh, 12 seconds here. Uh, not quite the 6 seconds as advertised, but still that\'s pretty fast. Overall, I\'d'

[01:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'say, you know, pretty solid generation here. Uh, you know, I didn\'t prompt for anything crazy, so we\'re more or less getting what we asked for. Uh, some nice camera movement with some kind of parallaxing effects there. Um, the characters are talking like I asked.'

[02:08] [scene:talk]
